cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with rectification of planar objects using computer vision techniques. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper involves estimation of camera rotation and homography for rectification of images, which falls under the domain of computer graphics. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed method can be used for object orientation estimation during surgeries with radiograph of osteosynthesis implants, which is related to robotics. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The rectification of images can be useful in multimedia applications such as document scanning and image processing. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The optimization function used for estimating vanishing points can be considered as an AI technique.
